            "kjv_def": "ask,\n bid, boast, call, describe, give out, name, put forth, say(-ing, on),\n shew, speak, tell, utter.",
            "pspeech": "V-PPM/P-NMS",
            "description": " properly, to \"lay\" forth, i.e. (figuratively) relate (in words (usually of systematic or set discourse; whereas \u1f14\u03c0\u03c9(\u00e9p\u014d) and \u03c6\u03b7\u03bc\u1f77(ph\u0113m\u00ed) generally refer to an individual expression or speech respectively; while \u1f10\u03c1\u1f73\u03c9(er\u00e9\u014d) is properly to break silence merely, and \u03bb\u03b1\u03bb\u1f73\u03c9(lal\u00e9\u014d) means an extended or random harangue)); by implication, to mean"
